>The whole thing was ramshackle, there was a lot of loose fiberglass pieces strewn across the non-skating areas, and the building smelled like mold and dust and wood.
>The vandals sprayed graffiti on every wall until the tags connected to make one enormous mural spanning multiple walls.
>Anyway, let's call the guy Lester and the Girl, Madison (they didn't have names in the dream)
>Lester was a 25-year-old pothead, he worked some shitty minimum wage job to get by, the whole bum ordeal.

>Lester had this nice little setup on what was the 2nd story, just sitting on an overhang made by few planks of plywood. His feet dangled off of the edge and you could oversee a lot of the park from the position.
>You could also see through a window into the empty lot behind the building, and I think there were some woods beyond that.
